ntion-and-failing-ci-prs/SKILL.md:3:description: Close batches of graalvm-reachability-metadata pull requests that either have the `human-intervention` label or failing CI, and revert their linked issues by clearing assignees and moving project status to `Todo`.\n./skills/close-human-intervention-and-failing-ci-prs/SKILL.md:15:Target open PRs in `oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata` when either condition\n./skills/close-human-intervention-and-failing-ci-prs/SKILL.md:31:     gh pr list -R oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata --state open --label human-intervention --limit 200 --json number,title,url,labels,statusCheckRollup\n./skills/close-human-intervention-and-failing-ci-prs/SKILL.md:35:     gh pr list -R oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata --state open --limit 500 --json number,title,url,labels,statusCheckRollup\n./skills/close-human-intervention-and-failing-ci-prs/SKILL.md:44:   gh pr view PR_NUMBER -R oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata --json number,title,state,merged,labels,statusCheckRollup,url,body\n./skills/close-human-intervention-and-failing-ci-prs/SKILL.md:56:         repository(owner: \"oracle\", name: \"graalvm-reachability-metadata\") {\n./skills/close-human-intervention-and-failing-ci-prs/SKILL.md:78:     gh issue view ISSUE_NUMBER -R oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata --json assignees,projectItems,state,title,url\n./skills/close-human-intervention-and-failing-ci-prs/SKILL.md:82:     gh issue edit ISSUE_NUMBER -R oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata --remove-assignee login1,login2\n./skills/close-human-intervention-and-failing-ci-prs/SKILL.md:87:     gh api repos/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/ISSUE_NUMBER -X PATCH -f assignees[]=\n./skills/close-human-intervention-and-failing-ci-prs/SKILL.md:94:         repository(owner: \"oracle\", name: \"graalvm-reachability-metadata\") {\n./skills/close-human-intervention-and-failing-ci-prs/SKILL.md:147:     gh pr close PR_NUMBER -R oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata --comment \"Closing this PR because CI is failing and returning the linked issue to Todo.\"\n./skills/close-human-intervention-and-failing-ci-prs/SKILL.md:150:     gh pr close PR_NUMBER -R oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata --comment \"Closing this human-intervention PR and returning the linked issue to Todo.\"\n./skills/close-human-intervention-and-failing-ci-prs/SKILL.md:157:     gh issue view ISSUE_NUMBER -R oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata --json assignees,projectItems,state,url\n./skills/close-human-intervention-and-failing-ci-prs/SKILL.md:158:     gh pr view PR_NUMBER -R oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata --json state,url\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `fixes-java-run-fail` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR described as `fixes-java-run-fail` or one that fixes Java/JVM runtime test failures for an existing library version update. Focus on validating the Java runtime fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:9:These PRs repair tests, dependencies, or narrow runtime setup after an existing library version compiles, but the JVM-based test fails when it runs. Review them more lightly than `library-new-request` PRs: the library already exists, so the goal is to restore Java runtime behavior for the new version while preserving meaningful test and dynamic-access coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:11:The PR number or URL can be passed as an optional argument (for example, `1234`, `https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/pull/1234`). If the user says \"review this PR\" without an argument, infer the PR from the surrounding conversation or `gh pr status`; only ask the user when it cannot be inferred. Use `gh pr view <pr>`, `gh pr diff <pr>`, and `gh pr checks <pr>` against the resolved PR throughout the workflow below.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:20:- Treat dynamic-access coverage preservation as the main quality gate. The new version should not report lower dynamic-access coverage than the previously tested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:21:- For numeric gates, compare the reported evidence as-is. Do not inspect generation filters, agent configuration, or metadata contents to second-guess why dynamic-access or metadata-count numbers are what they are.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:23:- Accept only `reachability-metadata.json` files as metadata files. Reject legacy native-image metadata config files such as `reflect-config.json`, `resource-config.json`, `proxy-config.json`, `serialization-config.json`, `jni-config.json`, or `predefined-classes-config.json`.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:36:     - `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/<new-version>/reachability-metadata.json`\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:41:   - Treat a new `reachability-metadata.json` for the tested version as normal for this label, including `{}` when validation and stats are coherent.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:45:   - Reject legacy native-image metadata config files. Metadata for generated support and test-only metadata must use `reachability-metadata.json`.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:56:4. Check dynamic-access coverage across versions.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:59:   - Do not use `user-code-filter.json`, agent configuration, or metadata file contents to argue that the reported dynamic-access values are not comparable. Use the stats values as reported unless the stats are missing or stale.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:60:   - A lower `coverageRatio` or lower `coveredCalls` for the new version is blocking unless the total dynamic-access surface changed and the PR explains why the reduction is expected.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:69:   - Do not require an exact match. Differences are normal when upstream APIs move, generated metadata is cleaned up, or dynamic-access totals change.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:71:   - When the new total is below 25% of the original and the tests and dynamic-access stats still claim comparable coverage, ask for restored metadata or a concrete explanation of the API/runtime-surface change.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:110:- For coverage drops: say that dynamic-access coverage must not regress between tested versions, cite the old and new values, and ask for either restored coverage or a concrete explanation.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:118:- For legacy metadata files: say that metadata must use `reachability-metadata.json` and ask for old config files such as `reflect-config.json` or `resource-config.json` to be replaced.\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck.gradle:36:        // Restrict cacheability to the dynamic-access reporting lane.\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck.gradle:37:        task.outputs.cacheIf(\"Enabled only when generating dynamic-access reports\") {\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck.gradle:154:boolean nativeTraceImageTaskRequested = !informationalTaskRequested &&\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck.gradle:155:        (isTaskRequested(\"nativeTraceImage\") || isTaskRequested(\"runNativeTraceImage\"))\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck.gradle:156:boolean runNativeTraceImageTaskRequested = !informationalTaskRequested && isTaskRequested(\"runNativeTraceImage\")\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck.gradle:221:if (runNativeTraceImageTaskRequested) {\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck.gradle:224:if (nativeTraceImageTaskRequested && project.hasProperty(\"metadataConfigDirs\")) {\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck.gradle:311:Provider<Directory> dynamicAccessOutputDir = layout.buildDirectory.dir(\"native/nativeTestCompile/dynamic-access\")\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck.gradle:314:    task.setDescription(\"Builds native tests with dynamic-access tracking and reuses Gradle up-to-date checks when inputs and classpath are unchanged\")\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck.gradle:338:    if (nativeTraceImageTaskRequested) {\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck.gradle:340:        buildArgs.add(\"-H:+MetadataTracingSupport\")\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck.gradle:345:            (nativeTraceImageTaskRequested || nativeTestTaskRequested)\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck.gradle:349:    if (runNativeTraceImageTaskRequested) {\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck.gradle:350:        // The verification gate runs runNativeTraceImage in its correction\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck.gradle:356:        buildArgs.add(\"--exact-reachability-metadata\")\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck.gradle:368:        if (runNativeTraceImageTaskRequested) {\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck.gradle:422:tasks.register(\"nativeTraceImage\") { task ->\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck.gradle:428:tasks.register(\"runNativeTraceImage\", Exec) { Exec task ->\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck.gradle:431:    task.dependsOn(tasks.named(\"nativeTraceImage\"))\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `fixes-javac-fail` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR that fixes Java compilation failures for an existing library version update. Focus on validating the compile fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:11:The PR number or URL can be passed as an optional argument (for example, `1234`, `https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/pull/1234`). If the user says \"review this PR\" without an argument, infer the PR from the surrounding conversation or `gh pr status`; only ask the user when it cannot be inferred. Use `gh pr view <pr>`, `gh pr diff <pr>`, and `gh pr checks <pr>` against the resolved PR throughout the workflow below.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:20:- Treat dynamic-access coverage preservation as the main quality gate. The new version should not report lower dynamic-access coverage than the previously tested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:21:- For numeric gates, compare the reported evidence as-is. Do not inspect generation filters, agent configuration, or metadata contents to second-guess why dynamic-access or metadata-count numbers are what they are.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:23:- Accept only `reachability-metadata.json` files as metadata files. Reject legacy native-image metadata config files such as `reflect-config.json`, `resource-config.json`, `proxy-config.json`, `serialization-config.json`, `jni-config.json`, or `predefined-classes-config.json`.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:36:     - `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/<new-version>/reachability-metadata.json`\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:41:   - Treat a new `reachability-metadata.json` for the tested version as normal for this label, including `{}` when validation and stats are coherent.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:44:   - Reject legacy native-image metadata config files. Metadata for generated support and test-only metadata must use `reachability-metadata.json`.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:54:4. Check dynamic-access coverage across versions.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:57:   - Do not use `user-code-filter.json`, agent configuration, or metadata file contents to argue that the reported dynamic-access values are not comparable. Use the stats values as reported unless the stats are missing or stale.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:58:   - A lower `coverageRatio` or lower `coveredCalls` for the new version is blocking unless the total dynamic-access surface changed and the PR explains why the reduction is expected.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:67:   - Do not require an exact match. Differences are normal when upstream APIs move, generated metadata is cleaned up, or dynamic-access totals change.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:69:   - When the new total is below 25% of the original and the tests and dynamic-access stats still claim comparable coverage, ask for restored metadata or a concrete explanation of the API/package change.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:107:- For coverage drops: say that dynamic-access coverage must not regress between tested versions, cite the old and new values, and ask for either restored coverage or a concrete explanation.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:114:- For legacy metadata files: say that metadata must use `reachability-metadata.json` and ask for old config files such as `reflect-config.json` or `resource-config.json` to be replaced.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `library-new-request` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR that adds metadata and tests for a new library, including PRs titled like `[GenAI] Add support for com.fasterxml:classmate:1.5.1 using gpt-5.4`. Focus on catching scaffold-only tests, version-pinned or package-bypassing tests, and PRs that push more than one library.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:11:The PR number or URL can be passed as an optional argument (for example, `1234`, `https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/pull/1234`). If the user says \"review this PR\" without an argument, infer the PR from the surrounding conversation (for example, an open review tab, a PR URL mentioned earlier, or the current branch's PR from `gh pr status`); only ask the user when it cannot be inferred. Use `gh pr view <pr>`, `gh pr diff <pr>`, and `gh pr checks <pr>` against the resolved PR throughout the workflow below.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:21:- Require reported dynamic-access coverage above 20% when there are dynamic-access calls to cover. Use the exploded stats files under `stats/<group>/<artifact>/<metadata-version>/stats.json` when available, and block the PR when dynamic-access coverage is 20% or lower or the PR provides no credible dynamic-access coverage evidence for non-zero dynamic-access calls.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:22:- Treat dynamic-access coverage counts as a minimum gate, not complete metadata evidence. They can miss metadata required through downstream libraries, so do not use high coverage alone to prove that the submitted metadata is complete or necessary.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:23:- Treat `0/0` dynamic-access coverage as a valid no-calls case, not as failed coverage. Do not reject a PR only because the exploded stats report `0/0` dynamic-access calls while the PR adds metadata; those stats can miss metadata required through downstream libraries.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:24:- Do not explicitly read or review individual metadata entries. Use the metadata entry count reported in the PR description for the metadata/dynamic-access mismatch check; do not manually count entries from metadata files. When the PR reports both library metadata entries and test-only metadata entries, use their sum as the PR-reported metadata entry count. Only request investigation when the covered dynamic-access call count is at least 75% higher than that PR-reported total.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:25:- Accept only `reachability-metadata.json` files as metadata files. Reject legacy native-image metadata config files such as `reflect-config.json`, `resource-config.json`, `proxy-config.json`, `serialization-config.json`, `jni-config.json`, or `predefined-classes-config.json`.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:38:     - `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/reachability-metadata.json`\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:44:   - Reject legacy native-image metadata config files. New-library metadata must be provided through `reachability-metadata.json`, including any test-only metadata under `tests/src/**`.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:56:   - Do not read, list, or reason from individual entries inside `reachability-metadata.json`.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:57:   - For metadata/dynamic-access mismatch checks, use only the metadata entry count reported in the PR description, such as `Metadata entries`, or legacy fields such as `Entries` and `Entries found` in older PRs; add `Test-only metadata entries` when the PR reports it; do not manually count metadata entries from files.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:58:   - Treat `reachability-metadata.json` containing `{}` as acceptable when the rest of the PR is coherent and validation passes.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:63:   - Confirm reported dynamic-access coverage is above 20% when the stats include dynamic-access calls.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:64:   - If the PR reports zero dynamic-access calls and `reachability-metadata.json` is `{}`, that is acceptable as long as the test is library-specific and the scope is otherwise correct.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:65:   - If the PR reports zero dynamic-access calls while adding metadata, do not reject it on that basis alone; dynamic-access stats can miss metadata required through downstream libraries.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:66:   - If the stats report 20% coverage or lower for non-zero dynamic-access calls, or no usable coverage signal for claimed dynamic-access behavior, ask for stronger tests or refreshed coverage evidence.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:67:   - Ask for metadata/coverage mismatch investigation only when the covered dynamic-access call count is at least 75% higher than the PR-reported metadata entry count, where the reported count is `Metadata entries` plus `Test-only metadata entries` when both are present. For older PRs, use legacy `Entries` or `Entries found` as the metadata entry count.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:90:  - Reported dynamic-access coverage is 20% or lower for non-zero dynamic-access calls, absent for claimed dynamic-access behavior, or not credible from the diff.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:101:- For insufficient dynamic-access coverage: say that new-library PRs need dynamic-access coverage above 20% when there are dynamic-access calls to cover, and ask for stronger tests or refreshed coverage evidence.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:103:- For metadata/dynamic-access entry mismatch: ask for investigation only when covered dynamic-access calls are at least 75% higher than the PR-reported metadata entry count, summing library and test-only metadata entries when both are reported. Do not manually count or argue from metadata contents.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:104:- For legacy metadata files: say that metadata must use `reachability-metadata.json` and ask for old config files such as `reflect-config.json` or `resource-config.json` to be replaced.\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:7:Fetches open issues from the graalvm-reachability-metadata project board,\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:13:      [--strategy-name <name>] [--reachability-metadata-path <path>]\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:15:      [--reachability-metadata-path <path>] [--review-model <model>] [--period <seconds|Nm|Nh|Nd>]\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:148:REPO = \"oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata\"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2413:    \"\"\"Load dynamic-access coverage from the stored run metrics stats block.\"\"\"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2443:    \"\"\"Resolve the dynamic-access coverage report path for a new-library issue.\"\"\"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2449:        \"dynamic-access\",\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2450:        \"dynamic-access-coverage.json\",\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2455:    \"\"\"Load dynamic-access coverage directly from the generated report as a fallback.\"\"\"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2585:        \"Analyze the generated tests, metadata, stats, and dynamic-access report in this repository. \"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2589:        \"- Explain briefly why dynamic-access coverage is missing or still very low.\\n\"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2608:        f\"Automation completed for `{claimed_issue.issue_coordinates}`, but dynamic-access coverage remains \"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2610:        \"This suggests the generated tests are not exercising the required dynamic-access paths well enough.\\n\\n\"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2612:        \"- Inspect the generated tests and compare them with the dynamic-access report to find uncovered call sites.\\n\"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:2755:        \"- Current reachability-metadata worktree\\n\"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:3373:            \"--reachability-metadata-path\", claimed_issue.worktree_path,\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:3379:            pipeline_argv.append(\"--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access\")\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:3401:            \"--reachability-metadata-path\", claimed_issue.worktree_path,\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:3426:            \"--reachability-metadata-path\", claimed_issue.worktree_path,\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:3451:            \"--reachability-metadata-path\", claimed_issue.worktree_path,\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:3472:            \"--reachability-metadata-path\", claimed_issue.worktree_path,\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:3854:    \"\"\"Create isolated worktrees for reachability-metadata and metrics storage.\"\"\"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:3880:    \"\"\"Remove the isolated issue worktrees for reachability-metadata and metrics.\"\"\"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:4020:        \"so Forge will not run reachability-metadata workflows for this artifact.\\n\\n\"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:4270:                    \"--reachability-metadata-path\", claimed_issue.worktree_path,\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:4278:                \"--reachability-metadata-path\", claimed_issue.worktree_path,\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:4290:                \"--reachability-metadata-path\", claimed_issue.worktree_path,\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:4301:                \"--reachability-metadata-path\", claimed_issue.worktree_path,\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:4312:                \"--reachability-metadata-path\", claimed_issue.worktree_path,\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:4322:                \"--reachability-metadata-path\", claimed_issue.worktree_path,\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:5478:        description=\"Resolve graalvm-reachability-metadata issues automatically.\"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:5517:        \"--reachability-metadata-path\",\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:5519:            \"Path to the graalvm-reachability-metadata repository. \"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:5541:        \"--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access\",\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:5544:            \"Forwarded to the new-library pipeline. Keeps generated tests for dynamic-access \"\n./forge/forge_metadata.py:5545:            \"strategies even when no dynamic-access coverage is added.\"\n./skills/fix-missing-reachability-metadata/SKILL.md:2:name: fix-missing-reachability-metadata\n./skills/fix-missing-reachability-metadata/SKILL.md:6:# Fix missing reachability metadata entries in the reachability-metadata.json\n./skills/fix-missing-reachability-metadata/SKILL.md:20:   - Copy the suggested JSON entry for the missing type into the corresponding section of the reachability-metadata.\n./skills/fix-missing-reachability-metadata/SKILL.md:22:   - Write to `metadata/<library-specific-metadata-directory>/reachability-metadata.json`.\n./skills/fix-missing-reachability-metadata/SKILL.md:47:add the following to the 'reflection' section of reachability-metadata.json:\n./skills/README.md:3:This directory contains all agent skills and workflows used for the `graalvm-reachability-metadata` project.\n./skills/README.md:9:### `fix-missing-reachability-metadata`\n./skills/README.md:12:It runs the target tests, identifies missing metadata entries from the error output, and adds them to the correct section of `reachability-metadata.json`. This process repeats until all required metadata is available and the tests pass.\n./skills/README.md:27:It covers compile-failure repair PRs for existing libraries and applies a lighter review than `library-new-request`: keep the diff scoped to the compile fix, preserve meaningful tests, and block regressions where dynamic-access coverage drops between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/README.md:32:It covers JVM runtime-failure repair PRs for existing libraries and applies a lighter review than `library-new-request`: keep the diff scoped to the Java runtime fix, preserve meaningful tests and assertions, and block regressions where dynamic-access coverage drops between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/README.md:37:It covers native-image runtime-failure repair PRs for existing libraries and applies a lighter review than `library-new-request`: verify the native path is fixed rather than skipped, keep metadata and test changes scoped, and block regressions where dynamic-access coverage drops between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/README.md:51:Creates a GitHub issue and pull request for `oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata`, links the PR to the issue, and requests reviews from the standard reviewers other than the PR author.\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/FixTestNativeImageRun.java:37:    private static final String REACHABILITY_METADATA_FILE = \"reachability-metadata.json\";\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `fixes-native-image-run-fail` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR that fixes a native-image runtime failure for an existing library version update. Focus on validating the runtime/native fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:9:These PRs repair metadata or tests after an existing library version compiles and builds a native image, but the native image fails when the test runs. Review them more lightly than `library-new-request` PRs: the library is already supported, so the goal is to restore native-image behavior for a newer version while preserving existing dynamic-access coverage.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:11:The PR number or URL can be passed as an optional argument (for example, `1234`, `https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/pull/1234`). If the user says \"review this PR\" without an argument, infer the PR from the surrounding conversation or `gh pr status`; only ask the user when it cannot be inferred. Use `gh pr view <pr>`, `gh pr diff <pr>`, and `gh pr checks <pr>` against the resolved PR throughout the workflow below.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:19:- Treat dynamic-access coverage preservation as the main quality gate. The new version should not report lower dynamic-access coverage than the previously tested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:20:- For numeric gates, compare the reported evidence as-is. Do not inspect generation filters, agent configuration, or metadata contents to second-guess why dynamic-access or metadata-count numbers are what they are.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:22:- Accept only `reachability-metadata.json` files as metadata files. Reject legacy native-image metadata config files such as `reflect-config.json`, `resource-config.json`, `proxy-config.json`, `serialization-config.json`, `jni-config.json`, or `predefined-classes-config.json`.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:35:     - `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/reachability-metadata.json`\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:44:   - Reject legacy native-image metadata config files. Metadata for generated support and test-only metadata must use `reachability-metadata.json`.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:53:4. Check dynamic-access coverage across versions.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:56:   - Do not use `user-code-filter.json`, agent configuration, or metadata file contents to argue that the reported dynamic-access values are not comparable. Use the stats values as reported unless the stats are missing or stale.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:57:   - A lower `coverageRatio` or lower `coveredCalls` for the new version is blocking unless the total dynamic-access surface changed and the PR explains why the reduction is expected.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:58:   - If metadata fixes make the native run pass but the dynamic-access ratio drops, ask for restored coverage first. Passing native execution is not enough by itself.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:67:   - Do not require an exact match. Differences are normal when upstream APIs move, generated metadata is cleaned up, or dynamic-access totals change.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:69:   - When the new total is below 25% of the original and the tests and dynamic-access stats still claim comparable coverage, ask for restored metadata or a concrete explanation of the API/package change.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:107:- For coverage drops: say that dynamic-access coverage must not regress between tested versions, cite the old and new values, and ask for either restored coverage or a concrete explanation.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:111:- For legacy metadata files: say that metadata must use `reachability-metadata.json` and ask for old config files such as `reflect-config.json` or `resource-config.json` to be replaced.\n./forge/utility_scripts/gradle_environment.py:17:    \"\"\"Return the isolated Gradle user home for a reachability-metadata worktree.\"\"\"\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/DockerTask.java:54:                    + new URI(\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#providing-the-tests-that-use-docker\"));\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/DockerTask.java:66:                        + new URI(\"https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#providing-the-tests-that-use-docker\"));\n./skills/close-new-library-support-pr/SKILL.md:3:description: Close or reject pull requests that add support for a new library in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to close a `library-new-request` PR and roll the linked issue back by removing assignees and changing project status from `In Progress` to `Todo` without downgrading `Done`.\n./skills/close-new-library-support-pr/SKILL.md:11:The PR number or URL can be passed as an optional argument (for exa